00:04:06,520 --> 00:04:08,512
An experiment was carried out

27
00:04:08,720 --> 00:04:11,838
to ascertain whether calcium
is soluble in water.

28
00:04:14,320 --> 00:04:17,950
First, a quantity of calcium
was obtained.

29
00:04:31,760 --> 00:04:36,755
Using a mortar and pestle, the
calcium is ground into a fine dust.

30
00:04:46,280 --> 00:04:49,557
The chalky dust
is poured into a beaker.

31
00:04:56,600 --> 00:04:59,672
Next, the beaker is placed
under a running tap.

32
00:05:00,040 --> 00:05:04,353
You can use distilled water,
but be aware of the cost.

33
00:05:05,800 --> 00:05:09,157
The calcium-water mixture
is agitated

34
00:05:09,360 --> 00:05:12,080
using a glass rod or pencil.

35
00:05:17,880 --> 00:05:20,952
It is then allowed
to settle for a while.

36
00:05:25,840 --> 00:05:29,231
So, is calcium soluble?

37
00:05:29,800 --> 00:05:32,872
Look closely
before making your decision.

38
00:05:37,880 --> 00:05:42,557
Have you observed the chalky
deposit at the base of the beaker?

39
00:05:42,720 --> 00:05:46,953
If you have, then you'll have
reached the conclusion that...

40
00:05:52,520 --> 00:05:54,910
There is a reason for this.

41
00:05:55,120 --> 00:05:57,112
Can you work out what it is?

42
00:05:58,840 --> 00:06:00,320
Correct.

43
00:06:00,480 --> 00:06:04,633
If calcium were soluble, our teeth
would be open to corrosion

44
00:06:04,840 --> 00:06:07,435
through daily contact with saliva.

45
00:06:07,600 --> 00:06:11,833
Again, man would be unable
to process foods

46
00:06:13,000 --> 00:06:15,310
and would starve.

47
00:06:17,400 --> 00:06:21,110
Here is a model
of a calcium molecule.

48
00:06:21,280 --> 00:06:23,920
Do you recognise the triple helix?

49
00:06:24,080 --> 00:06:27,039
If you do, write it down.

50
00:06:29,480 --> 00:06:32,279
The calcium molecule is built
on a semi-permanent structure

51
00:06:32,440 --> 00:06:36,320
of four electrons
supporting three protons.

52
00:06:37,440 --> 00:06:39,477
The protons feed
electrical information

53
00:06:39,680 --> 00:06:41,717
to the core of the molecule,

54
00:06:41,880 --> 00:06:45,669
where we find the central atom,
or "queen atom".

55
00:06:47,400 --> 00:06:50,837
Were the queen atom
to leave the molecule, or "nest",

56
00:06:51,040 --> 00:06:53,191
the effects would be disastrous,

57
00:06:53,360 --> 00:06:57,400
as the entire structure
would come tumbling down.

58
00:06:58,120 --> 00:07:01,238
This is known as
the Helvetica Scenario.

59
