137
00:13:34,400 --> 00:13:36,596
An experiment was carried out

138
00:13:36,760 --> 00:13:40,515
to observe the effects
of helium gas upon calcium.

139
00:13:40,680 --> 00:13:45,391
A pyramid of powdered calcium
is formed upon a work surface.

140
00:13:47,880 --> 00:13:50,236
Next, an ordinary ping-pong ball

141
00:13:50,440 --> 00:13:53,672
is placed carefully
on top of the pyramid.

142
00:13:58,280 --> 00:14:01,193
Now we mark the mid-point.

143
00:14:03,120 --> 00:14:08,275
Then helium gas is released
in the vicinity of the pyramid.

144
00:14:10,440 --> 00:14:12,511
As our starting pressure,

145
00:14:12,680 --> 00:14:16,594
we're using Cinderford's constant
of 2.5 quorums per second.

146
00:14:16,760 --> 00:14:23,075
Observe the reaction and note
the results down in your copybook.

147
00:14:28,760 --> 00:14:33,277
The pyramid of powdered calcium
has disappeared. Or has it?

148
00:14:41,800 --> 00:14:44,110
The calcium seems to have moved

149
00:14:44,320 --> 00:14:47,836
some eight inches away
from its original location.

150
00:14:49,440 --> 00:14:51,477
Eight inches.

151
00:14:53,800 --> 00:14:57,680
So, what's keeping
the ping-pong ball aloft?

152
00:14:59,360 --> 00:15:04,355
Surprisingly, the pyramid
of powdered calcium is still there.

153
00:15:04,560 --> 00:15:07,394
Only its image has moved.

154
00:15:07,560 --> 00:15:13,158
This phenomenon is known as
Calcic Image Misplacement, or CIM.

155
00:15:13,320 --> 00:15:17,155
Turn off the helium supply

156
00:15:17,320 --> 00:15:20,996
and the image of the pyramid
of powdered calcium

157
00:15:21,160 --> 00:15:24,836
is reunited with the actual pyramid
of powdered calcium.

158
00:15:25,720 --> 00:15:27,757
Now let's see what happens

159
00:15:27,960 --> 00:15:32,955
when we increase the flow
of helium by a factor of 5 qps.

160
00:15:34,600 --> 00:15:38,514
The pyramid's image
fades as before.

161
00:15:40,600 --> 00:15:46,278
This time it reappears
some 11.5 inches away.

162
00:15:46,440 --> 00:15:49,751
11.5. Write that down.

163
00:15:53,920 --> 00:15:57,118
Now we try a factor of 7.

164
00:16:00,960 --> 00:16:02,440
This time,

165
00:16:02,600 --> 00:16:06,879
